article.headline: Moore's 25 lead Drexel over Stony Brook 90-86
article.description: — Justin Moore had 25 points in Drexel's 90-86 win over Stony Brook on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Moore's 25 lead Drexel over Stony Brook 90-86
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — Justin Moore had 25 points in Drexel's 90-86 win over Stony Brook on Thursday night. Moore had six assists for the Dragons (19-11, 12-5 Coastal Athletic Association). Amari Williams scored 16 points while shooting 5 of 10 from the field and 6 for 9 from the line, and added eight rebounds and three steals. Luke House shot 3 for 6 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 8 of 9 from the free throw line to finish with 15 points. Dean Noll finished with 21 points for the Seawolves (16-14, 9-8). Tyler Stephenson-Moore added 20 points and two steals for Stony Brook. Keenan Fitzmorris also had 15 points and six rebounds. Moore scored 10 points in the first half and Drexel went into halftime trailing 35-30. Moore scored 15 points in the second half. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
